reviewText: This is for the Alpha 2016 DVD release. A tad washed out and overly light print with a nice Big Band soundtrack. Confusingly the quality falls apart mid way thru and it becomes pixelated for a few minutes. Quality goes back and forth after this from good to just ok. All things considered this is a very funny enjoyable film that is worth owning to see the lovely Ann Pennington with famous cross dresser Julian Eltinge.

I loved watching this movie because JULIAN ELTINGE starred in it and he is my first-cousin-once-removed ie my mother's first cousin. It was interesting to watch him impersonate a female. Dustin Hoffman used JULIAN ELTINGE as a role model for his part in TOOTSIE.

Entertaining film from a forgotten star. It is always great to see a film that you thought was lost. Excellent packaging, service and a great quality film all add up to a positive experience. Thank You.
